that social seclusion is a topic of paramount importance, especially across the eldest population. Almost 
9% of the people interviewed neither participate in any collective meeting nor have any kind of contact 
with society (telephone call, meeting, etc.) during a  " normal week " . As shown in the CNESPS-ISS, 
