about 37% of the CMHCs in the considered sample were involved in developing high-quality programmes 
focusing on continuity and care coordination for severe mental disorders. Tthese programmes included, for 
instance, intensive home care and drop-out prevention programmes. However, promotion and prevention 
programmes remained quite absent from most CMHCs, as only 18% had developed such programmes to a 
